rComments: GENERALLY i ENJOYED THE CLASS AND PROFESSOR SANTA CLAUS WAS REALLY HELPFUL. I ESPECIALLY APPRECIATED HOW HE SHOWED RESPECT FOR STUDENTS WHO WERE THERE PROMPTLY AND READY TO LEARN. THANK YOU.

Very good intro course to politics. Concepts were easy to understand. However, notes were not always posted, so find a friend. Midterm and exam were straightforward as long as you studied the material. Readings are vital in understanding concepts and doing well in essays.
SANTA

The professor is extremely clear, organized, and has a passion for the subject he teaches. . His rule of not being able to enter the classroom 10 minutes pass is very strict. He is also chubby and cute. :)
Extremely approachable! Goes way beyond class time to help students out!
Reasonable & approchable prof. get to know him. Such a passion for his academic interests. Willing to go above & beyond for his students. A+

This professor was awesome. The course material was fairly straightforward - if you just go to lectures you'll be able to get an A on the test/exam. I loved that he didn't let the late students in the class - you rock Prof. White

A great prof. to introduce you to Political Science. Very thankful that he insisted on some basic discipline with respect to timekeeping and courtesy unlike many of the weaker profs. I have encountered. Open minded and insightful. Jim Farney was an excellent TA!
very informative in the area of Canadian politics. Though Chris did not encourage participation in tutorial.  Prof reminds me of SANTA!
A really interesting prof; I think this guy deserves at least one chili pepper from a dozen ratings....He's lots of fun! Even if he is stuck on the "dont be late" issue
Clearly partisan. Likes to wave the Globe and Mail around. High strung.  Heâ€™s not a bad prof, but he reminds me of Taylor from the Gilmore Girls.

Prof White is a phenominal teacher. Sure, he is rather anal about coming late or leaving early, but the rest of us appreciate that. We managed to get there on time! Well-prepared (if not always with the latest bells and whistles), explains things superlatively, and will always listen to your opinions.  The highlight of an otherwise dull university!

Re: Jim Farney... He's actually a great T.A. who gives out marks when they're deserved.  If you can't write or think, perhaps why you didn't get the marks ;)  Professor White is excellent.  He knows his material, answers questions, gives easy tests (i.e. answer 4 of 8 questions), and half the material is common-sense.
He looks like Santa, but dont let that fool you. Dont ever be late for class, or dont ever ever think of leaving early.
This prof is a cutie petuttie. ..Yeah, he's tough - especially about arriving for his lectures on time. Who does he think he is? And he has a really wry sense of humour.
Good prof.  Tests are fair.  Some assignments are tough.  His courses are easy 70's but hard 80's.  Lectures are optional.

the prof is good, however his TA Jim is a nutcase. He reminds of a guy who didn't get enough loving from his parents. This sob flunks you for no reason, gives out the crappiest marks and darn if he's grading the Final. I have to say I was a lot more interested in the class before than after.
Just dont be late for class. For the love of God dont be late.

He is an excellent professor who knows his stuff.  His experience in the political arena can help any students who would like to persue a career in politics.  You will learn a lot, and enjoy attending his classes.

The most interesting thing about his lectures is that he always wears the same outfit.  Cargo pants with a flannel shirt.  Does he only have one outfit?  Or does he have a series of flannel shirts and cargo pants like Batman or something?
Good Prof, just don't be late for class.

Very knowledge and clear guy. Great sense of humour and loves taking pot shots at (all) politicians. Though the stuff he covers in lectures is mostly just brief summarization of the huge amount of course material reading assign. Still enjoyable though.
